{{one source|date=March 2015}} {{Spelling bee | name = 24th National Geographic Bee <!-- Commented out: | image = NationalGeographicBeeOfficialLogo.png --> | caption = | date = May 24, 2012 | location = [[Washington, D.C.]] | winner = Rahul Nagvekar | age = 14 | residence = [[Sugar Land, Texas]] | word = | contestants = 54 | moderator = | Preceded by = [[23rd National Geographic Bee]] | Followed by = [[25th National Geographic Bee]] }} The '''24th [[National Geographic Bee]]''' was held in [[Washington, D.C.]] on May 24, 2012, sponsored by the [[National Geographic Society]].
Fourteen-year-old Rahul Nagvekar, from [[Sugar Land, Texas]] won the competition, beating out 52 other competitors representing the 50 U.S. states, Pacific territories, and [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]] dependent schools.<ref>[http://www.nationalgeographic.com/geobee/2012-top-10-finalists/]</ref><ref>http://google-latlong.blogspot.com/2012/05/rahul-nagvekar-wins-2012-national.html</ref><ref>http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2012/05/texas-teen-wins-national-geographic-bee/</ref>
