{{Infobox Organization |name = Centers for International Business Education and Research |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = CIBER |motto = |formation =1988 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = International business education |headquarters = |location = |region_served =United States |membership = |language = |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization =U.S. Department of Education |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = $10,960,000 in 2008<ref name="mandate">[http://www.ed.gov/programs/iegpscibe/index.html U.S. Department of Education Program Description]</ref> |website = [http://ciberweb.msu.edu/ CIBERweb] |remarks = }}
The '''Centers for International Business Education and Research''' ('''CIBERs''') are resources for international [[business education]] in the United States funded by through the [[United States Department of Education]]. The centers were established in 1988 as part of the [[Omnibus Foreign Trade and Competitiveness Act|Omnibus Foreign Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988]]<ref name="Omnibus Foreign Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988">[http://thomas.loc.gov/cgi-bin/bdquery/R?d100:FLD002:@1(100+418) Omnibus Foreign Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988]</ref> As part of the legislation, CIBERs are mandated to provide six specific services<ref name="Executive">[http://ciberweb.msu.edu/NationalImpact/GrantProposalAbstracts2006-2010.pdf Executive Summary CIBER abstracts 2006-2010]</ref> among their services. There are CIBERs at 17 universities in the United States.<ref name="Executive" />
==CIBERS== *[http://marriottschool.byu.edu/gmc/ Brigham Young University] *[http://www.business.gwu.edu/CIBER/ George Washington University] *[http://ciber.gatech.edu/ Georgia Institute of Technology] *[http://ciber.gsu.edu/ Georgia State University] *[http://www.kelley.indiana.edu/CIBER/ Indiana University] *[http://global.broad.msu.edu/ Michigan State University] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20090228082030/http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/dept/ciber/ San Diego State University] *[http://www.fox.temple.edu/ciber/ Temple University] *[http://cibs.tamu.edu/ Texas A&M University] *[http://fisher.osu.edu/international/index.php?page=CIBER The Ohio State University] *[http://www.mccombs.utexas.edu/research/ciber/ The University of Texas at Austin] *[http://www.ed.gov/about/offices/list/ope/iegps/index.html U.S. Department of Education] *[http://www.ucdenver.edu/academics/InternationalPrograms/CIBER/Pages/IIB_CIBER.aspx University of Colorado at Denver] *[http://www.business.uconn.edu/CIBER/ University of Connecticut] *[http://www.rhsmith.umd.edu/ciber/ University of Maryland] *[http://www.bus.miami.edu/faculty-and-research/ciber/index.html University of Miami] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20090510101939/http://mooreschool.sc.edu/moore/ciber University of South Carolina] *[http://foster.washington.edu/ciber/ University of Washington]
