{{Italic title}} '''''Thulir''''' is an Indian monthly children's [[List of science magazines|science magazine]] published in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] by the [[Tamil Nadu Science Forum]] without a break since 1987.<ref>{{cite web|author=Shubashree Desikan|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-in-school/childrens-magazine-celebrates-silver-jubilee/article4135180.ece|title=Children’s magazine celebrates silver jubilee|work=The Hindu|date=26 November 2012|accessdate=28 December 2013}}</ref><ref name="saju">{{cite news|author1=M. T. Saju|title=25 years on, children's magazine going strong|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/25-years-on-childrens-magazine-going-strong/articleshow/17408957.cms|accessdate=29 July 2016|work=The Times of India|date=29 November 2012|location=Chennai}}</ref> Its purpose is to bring science to school children, especially in rural areas.<ref name="saju"/> The headquarters of the monthly is in [[Chennai]].<ref name="saju"/> ''Thulir'' is sustained by the support of children and [[teacher]]s.
